<body> <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode"> Dark Mode</button>
<div class="General">
<h3>1ST COMPLAINT: NASAL DISCHARGE (Rhinorrhea)</h3>
<!-- S: Site -->
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site
          &amp; Laterality</span> 
<ul>
<li><b>BILATERAL (Both sides):</b> <span class="infectious"></span></li>
<ul>
<li><span class="infectious">Viral URTI (Common Cold)</span>, <span class="rheumatic"></span></li>
<li><span class="rheumatic">Allergic Rhinitis</span></li>
</ul>
<li><b>UNILATERAL (One side):</b> <b class="oncology ent emergency">Red
              Flag.</b> Suggests a local cause: </li>
<ul>
<li><span class="General">Foreign Body (in children)</span>, <span class="oncology"></span></li>
<li><span class="oncology">Nasal Polyp, </span></li>
<li><span class="oncology"><b class="oncology">Tumor</b></span>, <span class="cns"></span></li>
<li><span class="cns">CSF Leak</span></li>
</ul>
</ul>
</div><span class="verbal">"Is the discharge coming
          from one side of your nose, or both?"</span></div>
<!-- O: Onset -->
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>

<ul>
<li>ACUTE (&lt; 4 weeks): <span class="infectious"></span></li>
<ul>
<li><span class="infectious">Viral URTI</span>, <span class="infectious"></span></li>
<li><span class="infectious">Acute Bacterial Sinusitis</span>, </li>
<li><span class="rheumatic">Seasonal Allergic Rhinitis</span></li>
</ul>
<li>CHRONIC (&gt; 12 weeks): <span class="rheumatic"></span></li>
<ul>
<li><span class="rheumatic">Perennial Allergic Rhinitis</span>, <span class="ent"></span></li>
<li><span class="ent">Chronic Rhinosinusitis</span>, <span class="ent"></span></li>
<li><span class="ent">Vasomotor Rhinitis</span></li>
<ol>
<li>ask about spray usage..!</li>
</ol>
</ul>
</ul>
</div><span class="verbal">"When did this start? Did it come on suddenly after
          being around someone who was sick, or with a change in season?"</span></div>
<!-- D: Duration -->
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration</span>

</div><span class="verbal">"How many days has this been going on for?"</span></div>
<!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>:
          Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span> 
<ul>
<li>AGGRAVATING: </li>
<ul>
<li>Pollen, dust mites, </li>
<li>animal dander, mold (Allergies); </li>
<li><strong>Temperature </strong>changes, </li>
<li>strong <strong>odors </strong>(Vasomotor Rhinitis).</li>
<li>sniffing tobacco</li>
<li><em>cocaine</em>!</li>
</ul>
<li>RELIEVING: </li>
<ul>
<li>Antihistamines, </li>
<li>nasal steroid sprays.</li>
</ul>
</ul>
</div><span class="verbal">"Does
          anything seem to trigger it, like pollen, dust, or pets? Does anything
          help, like antihistamines?"</span></div>
<!-- C: Character (THE KEY DIFFERENTIATOR) -->
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>:
          Character</span> 
<ul>
<li><b>Clear &amp; Watery (Profuse):</b> </li>
<ul>
<li><b class="rheumatic">Allergic Rhinitis</b>, </li>
<li><b class="infectious">Viral URTI (early stages)</b>, <span class="ent"></span></li>
<li><span class="ent">Vasomotor Rhinitis</span>, </li>
<li><b class="cns emergency">CSF Leak (if unilateral &amp; watery)</b></li>
</ul>
<li><b>Thick, Purulent (Yellow/Green):</b> </li>
<ul>
<li><span class="infectious">bacterial component (e.g., Acute
                Bacterial Sinusitis)</span> but can also be seen in later stages
              of viral cold.</li>
</ul>
<li><b>Mucoid (Thick, whitish/clear):</b> Later stages of a cold,
            Chronic Sinusitis.</li>
<li><b>Bloody (Epistaxis) or Blood-tinged:</b> </li>
<ul>
<li>Trauma, </li>
<li>dryness, </li>
<li> inflammation, or </li>
<li><b class="oncology emergency">Red Flag if unilateral</b>.</li>
</ul>
</ul>
</div><span class="verbal">"Can you describe the
          discharge? What color is it, and is it thin and watery or thick?"</span></div>
<!-- R: Radiation -->
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
          Radiation (of Pain)</span> 
<ul>
<li class="ent infectious">Facial pain/pressure is a key symptom of
            sinusitis.</li>
</ul>
</div><span class="verbal">"Do you have any pain
          or pressure in your face, for example in your cheeks or forehead?"</span></div>
<!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
          Associated Symptoms</span> 
<ul>
<li><b>ask other <br/>
</b></li>
<ul>
<li><b>Ear</b></li>
<li><b>Nose <br/>
</b></li>
<li><b>Throat</b></li>
</ul>
<li>trauma</li>
<li>flu</li>
<li>hay</li>
<li><b>Difficulty in breathing </b></li>
<ul>
<li><b>Nasal polyp</b></li>
<li><b>one nostril</b></li>
</ul>
<li><b>Post nasal drip</b></li>
<ul>
<li><b>nasal polyp<br/>
</b></li>
</ul>
<li><b>ALLERGIC CLUSTER:</b>
<ul>
<li class="rheumatic ophthalmology">Itchy eyes, nose, palate, or
                ears</li>
<li class="rheumatic ent">Sneezing (often in fits)</li>
<li class="rheumatic ophthalmology">Watery, red eyes (Allergic
                Conjunctivitis)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><b>VIRAL URTI CLUSTER:</b>
<ul>
<li class="infectious ent">Sore throat, cough</li>
<li class="infectious">Malaise, low-grade fever</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><b>ACUTE BACTERIAL SINUSITIS CLUSTER:</b>
<ul>
<li class="infectious ent">Facial pain or pressure (worse on
                bending forward)</li>
<li class="infectious ent">Reduced or absent sense of smell
                (Anosmia)</li>
<li class="infectious ent">Dental pain (upper teeth)</li>
<li class="infectious">High fever (&gt;38°C)</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</div><span class="verbal">"Along with the runny
          nose, have you had any itching, sneezing, fever, or a sore throat?"</span></div>
<!-- P: Progression -->
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
          Progression</span> 
<ul>
<li>"Double-sickening" (getting better then suddenly worse) is
            suggestive of secondary bacterial sinusitis.</li>
</ul>
</div><span class="verbal">"Has it changed since it
          started? For example, did it start clear and then become thick?"</span></div>
<!-- P: Pattern -->
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>

<ul>
<li>SEASONAL: <span class="rheumatic"></span></li>
<ul>
<li><span class="rheumatic">Allergic Rhinitis (pollen).</span></li>
</ul>
<li>PERENNIAL (Year-round): <span class="rheumatic"></span></li>
<ul>
<li><span class="rheumatic">Allergic Rhinitis (indoor allergens like
                dust mites).</span></li>
</ul>
<li>Worse in the morning: </li>
<ul>
<li>allergic and </li>
<li>vasomotor rhinitis.</li>
</ul>
</ul>
</div><span class="verbal">"Is there a pattern to it? For example, is it worse
          at certain times of the year?"</span></div>
<!-- E: Effect on life -->
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect
          on Life</span>  </div><span class="verbal">"How has this been affecting you?
          Is it disturbing your sleep or concentration?"</span></div>
<!-- R: Red Flags -->
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red
          Flags</span> 
<ul>
<li class="oncology ent emergency"><b>Persistent, unexplained
              unilateral symptoms</b> (discharge, bleeding, or blockage).</li>
<li class="cns emergency"><b>Clear, watery, unilateral discharge
              following a head injury.</b> (CSF Leak)</li>
<li class="cns emergency">Cancer sx</li>
<ul>
<li class="cns emergency">malignant nasal polyp </li>
</ul>
<li class="infectious emergency"><b>Signs of complicated sinusitis:</b>
<ul>
<li class="ophthalmology emergency">Periorbital swelling, redness,
                or pain</li>
<li class="ophthalmology cns emergency">Changes in vision (double
                vision, reduced acuity)</li>
<li class="cns emergency">Severe headache, altered mental status,
                or neck stiffness</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</div><span class="verbal">"I just need to ask some specific
          questions to make sure we're not missing anything serious."</span></div>
<!-- S: Scale -->
<div class="point"><div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity
          / Bother Scale</span>  </div><span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10,
          how much is this runny nose bothering you?"</span></div>
</div>
